{"cursor":"10492","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"The 'Royal Asiatic Society of Great Britain and Ireland' ('RAS') was\nestablished, according to its Royal Charter of 11 August 1824, to further \"the\ninvestigation of subjects connected with and for the encouragement of science,\nliterature and the arts in relation to Asia.\" From its incorporation the Society\nhas been a forum, through lectures, its journal, and other publications, for\nscholarship relating to Asian culture and society of the highest level. It is\nthe United Kingdom's senior learned society in the field of Asian studies.\nFellows of the Society are elected regularly. Fellows include highly\naccomplished and notable scholars of Asian Studies, and are entitled to use the\nhonorific post-nominal letters FRAS.\n","linknr":192,"url":"Royal_Asiatic_Society","recorded":1362572661,"links":22,"instances":["elder","philologist","historian"],"pdf":[],"categories":["1824 establishments in the United Kingdom","Professional associations based in the United Kingdom","Learned societies of the United Kingdom","Ancient Near East organizations","Organisations based in the United Kingdom with royal patronage","Clubs and societies in London","Organizations established in 1824"],"headings":["History","Branches","Journal","Oriental Translation Fund of Great Britain and Ireland","President","Past presidents","See also","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4c/Wikisource-logo.svg/38px-Wikisource-logo.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["william_jones","philologist"],["gordon_johnson","historian"],["charles_watkin_williams-wynn","elder"]],"members":["william_jones","gordon_johnson"],"related":["Royal_Charter","United_Kingdom","Learned_society","Fellows_